    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Augsburg, 30 December 1550)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">They received news two days ago that Niklas von Salm had
                            died in Eger after a short illness. Before his death, he wrote to Oláh
                            that he wanted Oláh to be with him, and Oláh also wanted to be there,
                            but it was not to be. If he had been in Eger, he would have performed
                            his funeral; but he is still here, waiting for Queen Mary, and once she
                            arrives, they will travel to Vienna together. The members of the royal
                            family are well. He is waiting for a reply to two or three of his
                            letters from Nádasdy, to whom he sends his regards, together with his
                            wife.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Spectabilis et Magnifice Domine et Frater Observandissime,
                    servitiorum meorum commendationem! </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Hoc biduo venit huc fama dominum <persName>comitem a
                        Salm</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Niklas von Salm.</note> post aliquanti
                    temporis aegritudinem <placeName>Agriae</placeName><note xml:id="note.2"
                        >Eger.</note> mortuum esse, corpore exesum.<note xml:id="note.3">For a long
                        time, Salm’s time of death was dated February 1550 in the literature, based
                        on <hi rend="smallcap">Bergmann</hi> 1844, 228. He was buried on 15 January,
                        see Oppolitanus 1551. Based on this letter, news of his death arrived from
                        eger to Augsburg on 28 December, in other words, he must have died at the
                        beginning of December.</note> Doleo ex animo id hoc tempore contigisse, non
                    solum propter me, sed magis propter <persName>maiestatem regiam</persName>,
                    dominum nostrum clementissimum, sed quis fato resistere potest? Vereor, ne <add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">occulto Dei iudicio premamur, et ne</add>
                    pedum Sancti Adalberti eum pupugerit, et calice Sancti Ioannis impeditus fuerit.
                        <persName>Nadasdi</persName> non fuit ibi. Cupiebat pauper<note
                        xml:id="note.4">Sc. Niklas von Salm.</note> (ut paulo ante mortem ad me
                        scripserat)<note xml:id="note.5">We do not know this letter.</note> me ibi
                    cum eo esse, et ego quoque certe id plurimum voluissem, sed fata restitere. Si
                    eos comites habuisset, quos tempore occupationis <placeName>Agriae</placeName>,
                    credo, quietori fuisset animo. Sed quid frustra de morte eius lacrimamur omnes
                    nos, quoque idem manet finis, Deus animae illius misereatur. Si
                        <placeName>Agriae</placeName> fuissem, extremum illi funus peregissem, et
                    hoc, quod Christianus Christiano, episcopus mortuis debet, non praetermitto. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Nos adhuc hic haeremus. Exspectamus serenissimam
                        <persName>Mariam</persName> reginam <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">hoc
                        biduo</add>, qua adveniente confectisque rebus credo nos non admodum diu hic
                    moraturos, sed post unum mensem <placeName>Wiennam</placeName> versus
                        profecturos.<note xml:id="note.6">They only leave for Vienna in
                        March.</note> Imperator, regia maiestas, Maximilianus, Ferdinandus, princeps
                    Hispaniarum, principes nostri clementissimi ex clementia Dei optime <milestone
                        unit="pb"/>valent. Ego quoque mediocriter. Exspectabam ad binas aut ternas
                    litteras meas a Dominatione Vestra responsum, sed hactenus nullum habui. Deus
                    optimus maximus Dominationem Vestram cum domina
                        <persName>coniuge</persName><note xml:id="note.7">Orsolya Kanizsai.</note>
                    sua carissima, domina mea observandissima felicem conservare dignetur.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Ex <placeName>Augusta</placeName> 30. Decembris 1550.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">
                    <seg type="signature">Servitor et frater Agriensis etc. manu propria</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.6">Spectabili et magnifico domino Thomae Nadasdi comiti perpetuo terrae
                    Fogaras iudici curiae regiae maiestatis et supremo regni Hungariae capitaneo
                    etc. domino et fratri observandissimo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Ad manus proprias. Cito, cito, cito.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
